Parliament, Tuesday 17 September 2019 – The National Assembly will tomorrow hold a plenary to discuss ‘Building state capacity through insourcing of government and all state-owned companies' workers’ led by Mr Julius Malema leader of the Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF). The Minister of Trade and Industry Mr Ebrahim Patel will at the same sitting do a statement on ‘Brexit’ and its impact on South Africa’s economy. Other matters on the agenda are motions without notice, member’s statements and notices of motion. Details of the sitting are as follows:
	Date: Tuesday, 16 September 2019
	Venue: NA Chamber, Parliament
	Time: 14:00 Meanwhile, the NCOP permanent delegates are in their respective provinces on a week-long Provincial Week programme. Journalists and photographers who do not have Parliamentary media access permits and wish to cover the NA sitting should send their details (full name, ID/passport number and name of the media house) to Masego Dlula on 081 715 9398 or 021 403 8141. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Enquiries: Moloto Mothapo – 082 370 6930 (Alternatively - Manelisi Wolela 0760622180 Committees have the power to summons any person to appear before them to give evidence or produce documents. They may ask any person or institution to report to them and may receive petitions, representations or submissions from the public. They play a crucial role in the law-making process.Read more